    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const item = $input.first().json;\n\nconst prompt = `\nYou are an expert Computer Science professor and technical educator.\n\nAnalyze the following YouTube video.\n\nVideo Title:\n${item.title}\n\nChannel:\n${item.author_name}\n\nVideo URL:\n${item.video_url}\n\nTranscript:\n\n${item.content}\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON.\n\nThe JSON schema must be:\n\n{\n  \"summary\":\"\",\n  \"explanation\":\"\",\n  \"key_learnings\":[],\n  \"important_concepts\":[],\n  \"applications\":[]\n}\n\nRequirements:\n\n- Summary:\n  - 8-12 concise lines covering the complete video.\n\n- Explanation:\n  - Detailed and beginner-friendly.\n  - Explain every important topic in the same order as the video.\n  - Use simple language as if teaching a student.\n\n- Key Learnings:\n  - Exactly 8 items.\n\n- Important Concepts:\n  - Exactly 6 items.\n  - Each item should be a single string representing an important concept from the video.\n\n- Applications:\n  - Exactly 5 real-world applications.\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object.\nDo not write markdown.\nDo not use code fences.\n`;\n\nreturn [\n  {\n    json: {\n      prompt\n    }\n  }\n];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
