      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "3d9008bc-260a-40ca-b091-fea44eca7467",
      "name": "Sticky Note6"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## JS Code Node\n\nThis is a common node used in Production to clearly demonstrate your Ideas to any AI agent , so for that we use all the data we get to write a common JS code which will behave as a Prompt for the AI as it will generate an JSON which will be easily understanded by any AI Model",
        "height": 608,
        "color": "#66A725"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        1408,
        224
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "570e7e67-0990-4168-8885-357eeac32267",
      "name": "Sticky Note7"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## Alternate AI Agent for Common Coder's \n\nThere is one alternate node in n8n i.e. the AI Agent Node which is having multiple features , why I am using this node is because **To create a Commonly understandable workflow which is having only RESTapis and HTTP requests , so that anyone who is even beginner to workflow Realm and has worked only with the Traditional Frontend and Backend Codes could also be able to understand this and could imitate the same in the code too without using any dependency tool like N8N just use the API**\n\nThis is a paid API and you need to Put your Credentials , [Gemini API](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs) , You can use any Chat Model you want\n\n",
        "height": 912,
        "width": 256,
        "color": "#5732BD"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        1696,
        224
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "3671c9aa-41c0-4bb0-9f84-fc158d5304ea",
      "name": "Sticky Note8"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## JSON Parser\n\nYou can imitate the same flow in Backend using the Fetch API and then Run a .then and again await for the conversion of json to object , here we are doing the same\n",
        "height": 512,
        "width": 256,
        "color": "#B78B4E"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        2000,
        224
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "ba927afc-9cc5-4590-8d98-553efb841f95",
      "name": "Sticky Note9"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Filtering the Required Fields only\n\n\nThis is helpful as our Final Goal is to make a File of the Generated Report so for doing that Structurally we need to get a structured data first that's why i filter out the Category of data i had got after the agentic flow and the supadata API i had used , using that I could generate the HTML , XML , JSON or  any Structured structured data to convert that easily into a file without being manually modifying the structue of File\n",
